---
import "../styles/global.css";
import "../styles/faq.css";
import Header from "../components/Header/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer/Footer.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>FAQ | Broken Duck Studio</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <Header />

    <main class="faq-section">
      <div class="faq-container">
        <h1 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">What is Broken Duck Studio?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Broken Duck Studio is a creator-focused production space for YouTubers based in Chiang Mai. We offer memberships, workshops, equipment rentals, and production support to help creators grow their channels.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Where is the studio located?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">We're located in Mae Pu Kha, San Kamphaeng District — about 25 minutes from central Chiang Mai. Members receive exact directions after signup.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Who can become a member?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Membership is open to anyone actively working on a YouTube channel. You don’t need to be monetized yet, but you must be serious about creating content for YouTube.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Can I use the studio for content that’s not on YouTube?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes — but you must be actively running a YouTube channel to be eligible for membership. You're free to record anything you like, as long as you're using YouTube as a primary platform.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Is there an application process?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Right now, there’s no application — but we will require one in the future. When applications open, creators will need to share their channel and content goals.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">What’s included in a membership?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">All members get 24/7 access to studio spaces, high-speed internet, a sound booth, lockers, private booking, weekly workshops, monthly events, and 4 guest passes per month.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">How do I book a room or booth?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">All members can book rooms and gear through our internal booking system, which will be available through the member login portal.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">What are the Sunday workshops?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Workshops happen every Sunday from 1–4 PM. Topics range from editing and scripting to monetization and thumbnail design. They include breakout sessions, peer feedback, and hands-on help. The last Sunday of each month is a public event. <a href="/events">See event details</a>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Can I bring guests?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. All members receive 4 guest passes per month. Guests must be registered in advance and are only allowed during staffed hours or events.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Do you offer equipment rentals?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. We rent cameras, microphones, lighting kits, and teleprompters through our partner Green Light Studio. <a href="/rental">View rental list</a>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Do you offer full production packages?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. You can book a full day or half day session with a videographer, director, and creative support. These are perfect for high-quality content shoots. <a href="/packages">See package options</a>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">What’s the difference between monetized and non-monetized membership?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">All members get the same access. Monetized members receive a lower rate and can serve as mentors to newer creators. Non-monetized members are matched with a mentor from within the studio.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Do you offer support for growing channels?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Our mentorship model pairs monetized members with newer creators. Weekly workshops also focus on skill-building, strategy, and collaboration.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Will there be a member login area?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. A members-only area is coming soon with booking tools, premium resources, and creator discussion spaces. <a href="/login">Coming soon</a>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">Will you launch an MCN or partner program?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. We're working on a future MCN offering for monetized creators. It will include optional support with monetization, channel growth, and production. <a href="/partner">Learn more</a>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-entry">
          <div class="faq-question">How do I get started?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Go to the <a href="/membership">Membership</a> page, choose your plan, and confirm payment. You'll receive welcome info and access instructions right after.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
